      • query

        public long query(java.lang.String table,
                  java.lang.String attr,
                  double lower,
                  double higher,
                  boolean distinct)
        Returns approximate number of (unique) values in a given range.
        Parameters:
        table - Table to be queried. (Order/LineItem)
        attr - Attribute to be queried (e.g. totalprice/extendedprice)
        lower - The lower boundary of a range query.
        higher - The higher boundary of a range query.
        distinct - True, if number of unique values to be returned, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        The approximate number of (unique) values in a given range.
